{#
  /sanctions/by-sector — pillar page that pivots the OFAC SDN list
  by sector (military / economic / diplomatic / governance) instead of
  the default entity-type bucket (individuals / entities / vessels /
  aircraft).

  Why this page exists:
    GSC's #1 organic query in our first 3 months was literally
    "ofac sdn list current military, economic, diplomatic" — i.e. the
    user's mental model is sector-based, not entity-type-based. This
    page serves that exact intent and, via internal links, gets the
    full 410-page corpus indexed under sector queries that the
    bucket-based index pages don't rank for.

  Structure:
    - Header explains the pivot and the date freshness
    - 4 sector cards (count, label, description, top 6 names, "see all")
    - Footnote on classification methodology + cross-link to bucket view
#}
{% extends "_base.html.j2" %}
{% from "_cluster_nav.html.j2" import cluster_nav %}
{% from "_ofac_alert_signup.html.j2" import ofac_alert_signup, ofac_alert_css, ofac_alert_js %}

{% block head_extra %}
{{ ofac_alert_css() }}
<style>
  .sector-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 22px; margin: 28px 0 32px; }
  @media (min-width: 720px) { .sector-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; } }
  .sector-card { border: 1px solid var(--sr-gray-light); border-left: 4px solid var(--sr-blue); border-radius: 4px; padding: 22px 24px; background: var(--white); }
  .sector-card h2 { font-family: var(--font-serif); font-size: 22px; color: var(--sr-blue-dark); margin: 0 0 4px; }
  .sector-card .count { display: inline-block; background: var(--sr-blue); color: var(--white); padding: 2px 10px; border-radius: 12px; font-size: 12px; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 0.5px; margin-left: 8px; vertical-align: middle; }
  .sector-card .desc { color: var(--sr-dark-text); font-size: 14px; margin: 8px 0 14px; line-height: 1.55; }
  .sector-card .top-names { list-style: none; margin: 0 0 12px; padding: 0; }
  .sector-card .top-names li { font-size: 13px; padding: 4px 0; border-bottom: 1px dotted var(--sr-gray-light); }
  .sector-card .top-names li:last-child { border-bottom: 0; }
  .sector-card .top-names a { color: var(--sr-blue-dark); text-decoration: none; font-weight: 600; }
  .sector-card .top-names a:hover { color: var(--sr-red); }
  .sector-card .see-all { display: inline-block; margin-top: 6px; font-size: 13px; color: var(--sr-red); font-weight: 700; text-decoration: none; }
  .sector-card .see-all:hover { text-decoration: underline; }
  .freshness-row { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 18px; align-items: center; margin: 12px 0 0; padding: 10px 14px; background: var(--sr-gray-bg); border-left: 3px solid #2e7d32; font-size: 13px; color: var(--sr-gray-text); }
  .freshness-row strong { color: var(--sr-dark-text); }
</style>
{% endblock %}

{% block content %}
<div class="container-wide">
  <nav class="breadcrumbs" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
    <a href="/">Home</a>
    <span>›</span>
    <a href="/sanctions-tracker">OFAC Venezuela Sanctions</a>
    <span>›</span>
    <strong>By sector</strong>
  </nav>

  <article>
    <header>
      <div style="font-size:12px; text-transform:uppercase; letter-spacing:1.4px; color:var(--sr-red); font-weight:700;">
        Live tracker · Refreshed twice daily from US Treasury
      </div>
      <h1>OFAC Venezuela SDN List by Sector — Currently Sanctioned Military, Economic, Diplomatic &amp; Governance Officials</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">
        All {{ stats.total }} active OFAC Venezuela-program designations grouped by the sector they
        operate in: armed forces, financial &amp; oil-sector actors, foreign-affairs officials,
        and political &amp; judicial figures. Each name links to a permanent profile with OFAC
        program code, designation date, and biographical data.
      </p>
      <div class="freshness-row">
        <span><strong>Last classified:</strong> {{ today_human }}</span>
        <span><strong>Source:</strong> US Treasury OFAC SDN List</span>
        <span><strong>Programs covered:</strong> VENEZUELA, EO 13692, EO 13850, EO 13884</span>
      </div>
    </header>

    <div class="body">
      <p>
        OFAC's official SDN listing groups Venezuela-related designations only by entity
        type (<a href="/sanctions/individuals">individuals</a>,
        <a href="/sanctions/entities">entities</a>,
        <a href="/sanctions/vessels">vessels</a>,
        <a href="/sanctions/aircraft">aircraft</a>) and by executive order — neither view
        answers the most common compliance question, which is <em>"who are the
        currently-sanctioned military officials?"</em> or <em>"which Venezuelan banks
        are on the SDN list?"</em>. The four cards below answer that pivot.
      </p>

      <div class="sector-grid">
        {% for s in sectors %}
        <div class="sector-card">
          <h2>
            <a href="{{ s.url_path }}" style="color:inherit; text-decoration:none;">{{ s.label }}</a>
            <span class="count">{{ s.count }}</span>
          </h2>
          <p class="desc">{{ s.description }}</p>
          {% if s.top_names %}
          <ul class="top-names">
            {% for p in s.top_names %}
            <li>
              <a href="{{ p.url_path }}">{{ p.display_name }}</a>
              <small style="color:var(--sr-gray-text); margin-left:6px;">— {{ p.program or 'Venezuela' }}</small>
            </li>
            {% endfor %}
          </ul>
          {% endif %}
          <a class="see-all" href="{{ s.url_path }}">See all {{ s.count }} {{ s.label|lower }} →</a>
        </div>
        {% endfor %}
      </div>

      <h2>How we classify each designation</h2>
      <p>
        Sector membership is computed from the OFAC remarks blob (which sometimes
        carries a job title like <em>"Minister of Defense"</em> or <em>"Bolivarian
        National Guard"</em>) and a curated overrides table for high-profile
        designations whose role is not in the SDN listing itself. Every profile
        belongs to exactly one sector — see the
        <a href="https://github.com/jonathanteplitsky/venezuela-investment-journal/blob/main/src/data/sdn_profiles.py" rel="nofollow">classifier source</a>
        if you want to inspect the keyword rules. For the OFAC-canonical view by
        entity type, use the <a href="/sanctions-tracker">sanctions tracker</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>Other ways to slice the list</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="/sanctions/individuals">All {{ stats.individuals }} sanctioned individuals (A–Z)</a></li>
        <li><a href="/sanctions/entities">All {{ stats.entities }} sanctioned entities and companies (A–Z)</a></li>
        <li><a href="/sanctions/vessels">All {{ stats.vessels }} blocked vessels</a></li>
        <li><a href="/sanctions/aircraft">All {{ stats.aircraft }} blocked aircraft</a></li>
        <li><a href="/tools/ofac-venezuela-sanctions-checker">Search any name against the live SDN list</a></li>
        <li><a href="/tools/ofac-venezuela-general-licenses">Active OFAC General Licenses for Venezuela</a></li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </article>

  {{ ofac_alert_signup(
       headline="Get notified when SDN designations change",
       note="New listings, delistings, and modifications to Venezuela-program entries — delivered within hours.",
       interests=["sdn_changes"],
       source="sanctions_by_sector_index"
  ) }}

  {{ cluster_nav(cluster_ctx) }}
  {{ ofac_alert_js() }}
</div>
{% endblock %}
